id: pm-uuee
title: pm install <invalid> lacks did-you-mean for built-in aliases
description: "Dogfood 2026-05-17: `pm install nonexistent` treats every name as a filesystem path: `Local extension source does not exist: \"<cwd>/<name>\"`. Built-in packages calendar/templates/guide-shell/todos/etc. should be suggested via fuzzy match when the name is close to a known alias. Improves agent recovery."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[4]: agent-ux,cli,did-you-mean,install
created_at: "2026-05-17T06:47:18.769Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-17T07:05:41.076Z"
deadline: "2026-05-22T06:47:18.769Z"
author: maintainer-agent
close_reason: "Deferring: low impact vs effort. Built-in alias fuzzy match would require enumerating bundled package catalog and computing distance. Track as future enhancement; current Local extension source does not exist error is acceptable and unambiguous."
body: ""
